    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_cyrt" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cyrt</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cirt</orth></form>
                <sense n="1" xml:id="sense_cyrt.1"><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>надмогильный камень</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>tombstone</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>памятник</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>monument</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <sense n="2" xml:id="sense_cyrt.2" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><abv:tr
                        xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>могила</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>grave</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cyrtcævæn</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cirtcævæn</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>надгробный камень</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>gravestone</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>nīḱīwal zonʒæn mæ cyrt</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>никто уж не будет знать моего надгробного камня</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>no one will know my tombstone</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>21</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Balsægy calx dyn mærdty fældyst fæwæd… wælæwyl ta dyn cyrf
                            wyʒæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>колесо Балсага да будет тебе посвящено в царстве мертвых, а в этом
                                мире пусть служит тебе надгробным памятником</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>May the Balsag's wheel be dedicated to you in the nether world, and
                                in this world let it serve you as a gravestone</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Нарт._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>150</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>amardi Ḱermen, æmæ jæ ællastoj sæ xæʒarmæ æmæ jyl ystyr cyrt
                            samadtoj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>умер Чермен, и привезли его домой и соорудили над ним большое
                                надгробие</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Chermen died, and they brought him home and built a large tombstone
                                over him</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>180</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ku ʽj ramaroncæ wædta in cirt skʼaxuncæ æma ʽj omi bajværuncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>когда его убивают, то копают ему могилу и укладывают его туда</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>when they kill him, they dig his grave and put him there</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Диг._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>61</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>babaj cirt min ka baxwaja?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кто постучится мне в могилу отца?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>who will knock on my father's grave?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>22</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>mæ cæsti sugæj ænæxaj kæd æj æ cirtʒævæn dær</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>моих слез лишен его надгробный камень</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>his gravestone lacks my tears</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Sozur"/><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">— „К самым простым по виду надмогильным
                    памятникам принадлежат распространенные повсюду в крае вертикальные плиты
                        (<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>cyrt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>čurt</w></mentioned>) с рельефными надписями и орнаментами и без них“
                            (<bibl><author>Л. Семенов</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Изв. Инг.
                            инст. I 196</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Proceedings of Ingush
                            research institute. I 196</biblScope></bibl>).</note>
                <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">— “The vertical slabs widespread throughout the
                    region (<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>cyrt</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>čurt</w></mentioned>) either with bold superscription and ornaments or
                    without it belong to the simplest grave monuments” (<bibl><author>L.
                            Semenov.</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Изв. Инг. инст. I
                            196</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Proceedings of Ingush Research
                            Institute. I 196</biblScope></bibl>).</note>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Остается в силе разъяснение Вс. %sМиллера%s (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                        55</biblScope></bibl>): к <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>čiϑra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>знак</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="xln"><lang/>
                        <w>τςηρϑε</w>
                        <gloss><q>памятник</q></gloss></mentioned> в Зеленчукской надписи,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>čihra</w>
                        <gloss><q>лицо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>образ</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>изображение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>cēr</w>
                        <gloss><q>подобный</q></gloss></mentioned><note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT
                        NOTE HERE </note>
                    <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>tcira-</w>
                        <gloss><q>изображение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>čiϑra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>видимый знак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>образ</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čitra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>видимый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>яркий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>пестрый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                            ><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">субстантивно</note>
                        <gloss><q>картина</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>изображение</q></gloss></mentioned>. Развитие значения (‘картина’,
                    ‘знак’, ‘надмогильный знак’) не нуждается в пояснениях. — К осетинскому
                    примыкают <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/>
                        <w>čirt</w>
                        <gloss><q>куча камней</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/>
                        <w>čurt</w>
                        <gloss><q>надмогильный камень</q></gloss></mentioned>. %n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                        55</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>267, 298</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Ws. %sMiller%s's explanation remains in force (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                        55</biblScope></bibl>): to <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>čiϑra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>sign</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="xln"><lang/>
                        <w>τςηρϑε</w>
                        <gloss><q>monument</q></gloss></mentioned> in Zelenchuk inscription,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>čihra</w>
                        <gloss><q>face</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>figure</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>image</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>cēr</w>
                        <gloss><q>alike</q></gloss></mentioned>,<note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT
                        NOTE HERE </note>
                    <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>tcira-</w>
                        <gloss><q>image</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>čiϑra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>visible sign</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>figure</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čitra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>visible</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>bright</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>motley</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="ru">субстантивно</note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en">as a substantive</note>
                        <gloss><q>picture</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>image</q></gloss></mentioned>. The development of the meaning
                    (‘picture’, ‘sign’, ‘tombstone’) does not need explanations. — The following
                    words are close to the Ossetic one: <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/>
                        <w>čirt</w>
                        <gloss><q>pile of stones</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/>
                        <w>čurt</w>
                        <gloss><q>tombstone</q></gloss></mentioned>. %n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 55</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>267,
                            298</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1">Может быть, сюда же <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>cəlai</w>
                        <gloss><q>куча камней как надмогильное сооружение</q></gloss></mentioned>
                    (ср.: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"
                            /><biblScope>17</biblScope></bibl>).</note>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1">Maybe <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>cəlai</w>
                        <gloss><q>pile of stones as a gravestone</q></gloss></mentioned> also refers
                    here (cf.: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"
                            /><biblScope>17</biblScope></bibl>).</note>
            </entry>
